# Web MVC com autenticacao e observabilidade

## 1) Objetivo
Padronizar projetos ASP.NET Core MVC com autenticacao/autorizacao e observabilidade.

## 2) Estrutura de pastas
```
src/
  Presentation/
    Controllers/
    Views/
    ViewModels/
    Program.cs
  Application/
    Interfaces/
    Services/
    DTOs/
    Validators/
  Domain/
    Entities/
  Infrastructure/
    Identity/
    Data/
      Context/
      Repositories/
    Observability/
  Tests/
    Unit/
    Integration/
```

## 3) Pacotes recomendados
- Microsoft.AspNetCore.Identity.EntityFrameworkCore
- Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.Cookies
- Serilog.AspNetCore
- OpenTelemetry.Extensions.Hosting
- MediatR
- FluentValidation
- Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore

## 4) Configuracao (Identity + DI)
```csharp
builder.Services.AddAuthentication()
    .AddCookie();

builder.Services.AddAuthorization(options =>
{
    options.AddPolicy("AdminOnly", p => p.RequireRole("Admin"));
});
```

## 5) Observabilidade
- Log de login/logout e falhas.
- Traces para endpoints criticos.

## 6) Seguranca e autorizacao
- Use Identity + password hashing.
- Use policy-based auth em controllers.

